remote Add new remote to local repository
git remote add new &lt;remote-url&gt;
branching New branch
git checkout -b &lt;new-branch&gt;
push branch on remote
git push -u origin &lt;branch&gt;
switch branch
git checkout &lt;branch&gt;
history check old commits and get their hash
git log
go back in time (definitive)
git reset --hard &lt;commit-hash&gt;
go back in time
git revert &lt;commit-hash&gt;
stash stash your current uncommited edits and go back to last commit-hash
